definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a pyrimidine ribonucleoside, a compound consisting of a pyrimidine base linked to ribose.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a deoxyribonucleotide, any compound consisting of a deoxyribonucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the deoxyribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a ribonucleotide, any compound consisting of a ribonucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the ribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a purine deoxyribonucleotide, any compound consisting of a purine deoxyribonucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the deoxyribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a purine ribonucleotide, any compound consisting of a purine ribonucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the ribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a pyrimidine deoxyribonucleotide, any compound consisting of a pyrimidine deoxyribonucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the deoxyribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a pyrimidine ribonucleotide, any compound consisting of a pyrimidine ribonucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the ribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an adenyl deoxyribonucleotide, any compound consisting of adenosine esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the deoxyribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an adenyl ribonucleotide, any compound consisting of adenosine esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the ribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a guanyl deoxyribonucleotide, any compound consisting of guanosine esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the deoxyribose moiety.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a guanyl ribonucleotide, any compound consisting of guanosine esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the ribose moiety.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dAMP, deoxyadenosine monophosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dADP, deoxyadenosine diphosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dATP, deoxyadenosine triphosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dGMP, deoxyguanosine monophosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dGDP, deoxyguanosine diphosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dGTP, deoxyguanosine triphosphate.
Catalysis of the unwinding of an RNA helix in the direction 5' to 3'.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate -  this reaction drives the unwinding of an RNA helix in the direction 5' to 3'.
Catalysis of the transfer of a linoleoyl ((9Z,12Z)-octadeca-9,12-dienoyl) group to an oxygen atom on the acceptor molecule.
Catalysis of the transfer of a linoleoyl ((9Z,12Z)-octadeca-9,12-dienoyl) group from phosphatidylcholine to an oxygen atom on a cardiolipin molecule.
The lipid bilayer surrounding an aleurone grain.

A fibrous network that is part of the hyalin layer extracellular matrix. The apical lamina is thought to be principally composed of the glycoproteins fibropellins. This matrix has been found in echinoderms.
The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the thin, flattened compartments that form the central portion of the Golgi complex.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a growth cone.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a multivesicular body.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a protein storage vacuole.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a ruffle.
The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments that make up the trans-Golgi network.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a neuron projection.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a dendrite.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a dendritic spine.

The component of the mitochondrial membrane consisting of the gene products that have some part that penetrates at least one leaflet of the membrane bilayer. This component includes gene products that are buried in the bilayer with no exposure outside the bilayer.
A small membrane-bounded vesicle that releases its contents by exocytosis in response to insulin stimulation -  the contents are enriched in GLUT4, IRAP and VAMP2.

A heterotrimeric protein complex formed by the association of NHE3, E3KARP and alpha-actinin upon an increase in calcium ion concentration -  found in clusters localized on plasma membrane and in intracellular compartments.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any protein or protein complex (a complex of two or more proteins that may include other nonprotein molecules), in the presence of copper.
The covalent transfer of a methyl group to N-6 of adenine in a DNA molecule.
The covalent transfer of a methyl group to C-5 or N-4 of cytosine in a DNA molecule.

A heterotrimeric H4|H2A histone acetyltransferase complex with a substrate preference of chromatin over free histones. It contains a subset of the proteins found in the larger NuA4 histone acetyltransferase complex -  for example, the S. cerevisiae complex contains Esa1p, Yng2p, and Epl1p.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + cobalt(out) -eq- ADP + phosphate + cobalt(in).
A heterodimeric protein complex that acts as an RNA polymerase II elongation factor -  the complex is conserved from yeast to humans, and is present in S. pombe, but absent from S. cerevisiae.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription elongation, the extension of an RNA molecule after transcription initiation and promoter clearance by the addition of ribonucleotides catalyzed by a DNA-dependent RNA polymerase.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA-templated transcription, elongation

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of transcription elongation, the extension of an RNA molecule after transcription initiation and promoter clearance by the addition of ribonucleotides catalyzed by a DNA-dependent RNA polymerase.

label.value: positive regulation of DNA-templated transcription, elongation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription elongation, the extension of an RNA molecule after transcription initiation and promoter clearance by the addition of ribonucleotides catalyzed by a DNA-dependent RNA polymerase.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with lead (Pb) ions.

label.value: negative regulation of CREB transcription factor activity

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of the transcription factor CREB.

label.value: positive regulation of CREB transcription factor activity

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of activity of the transcription factor CREB.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a GTPase activating protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a heterotrimeric G-protein.

A protein complex that contains the survival motor neuron (SMN) protein and at least eight additional integral components, including the Gemin2-8 and Unrip proteins -  the complex is found in the cytoplasm and in nuclear Gems, and is involved in spliceosomal snRNP assembly in the cytoplasm and in pre-mRNA splicing in the nucleus.
